      "acceptanceCriteria": "Version-controlled solver with documented test suite covering hemolysis-relevant flow regimes; formal release validation record required at MRL 5.",
      "rationale": "The CFD solver is under version control and has a basic regression test suite, but no formal release validation record specific to hemolysis-relevant turbulent rotating flows exists. Achieved level 2 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Order-of-accuracy verification using manufactured solutions for rotating turbulent flow; demonstration that solver achieves expected convergence rates.",
      "rationale": "Code verification was performed for laminar pipe flow only. No manufactured solution verification exists for the rotating turbulent flow regime relevant to the VAD pump. Achieved level 2 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Richardson extrapolation or equivalent grid convergence study on hemolysis index QOI using at least three systematically refined meshes; GCI reported.",
      "rationale": "A two-mesh comparison was performed showing less than 3% variation in hemolysis index; however, Richardson extrapolation requires a minimum of three meshes and GCI was not computed. Achieved level 2 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions replicate VAD operating envelope including rotational speed range, flow rate range, and blood analogue properties; uncertainty in test conditions quantified.",
      "rationale": "FDA pump experiments were conducted at overlapping but not fully matching flow-speed combinations relative to the VAD COU envelope. Blood analogue viscosity uncertainty was partially characterized. Achieved level 3 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., E_rel or U95 validation metric) computed for hemolysis index across all operating points; metric threshold defined a priori.",
      "rationale": "Comparison was performed graphically without a pre-specified quantitative acceptance threshold for the hemolysis index. Systematic over-prediction at low flow rates was noted but not formally evaluated against a metric. Achieved level 2 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
