      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent review of simulation setup, boundary condition assignment, and post-processing scripts by a qualified analyst not involved in model development.",
      "rationale": "No independent review of simulation setup or post-processing was performed. All simulation runs and result extraction were conducted by the same analyst team. Achieved level 1 against required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Formal justification for selection of turbulence model and hemolysis damage accumulation model; sensitivity of hemolysis index to model form choices quantified.",
      "rationale": "The SST k-omega turbulence model was selected without documented comparison to alternative turbulence models for rotating blood pump flows. Model form sensitivity to hemolysis power-law exponent was not quantified. Achieved level 1 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All material properties and boundary conditions characterised with uncertainty bounds; Monte Carlo propagation completed and sensitivity indices reported for hemolysis index.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo UQ was initiated but only two input parameters (inlet velocity and blood viscosity) were varied. Rotational speed uncertainty, outlet pressure uncertainty, and hemolysis model constants were treated as deterministic. Achieved level 1 against required level 4."
    },
